title: Cape Soccer Turns Up Heat Lightning Beats Delmar 3 -0
text: Cape Soccer Turns Up Heat Lightning Beats Delmar 3 -0 Game called at 42 minute mark Oct 13, 2015 Photo by: Dan Cook Cape senior captain Drew Mulcahy gets airborne to control the ball past Delmar goalkeeper Damarius Kelley. The Cape soccer team defeated Delmar Tuesday night ,October 13, at Legends Stadium 3 to 0 in a game called at the 42 minute mark due to lightning which was pretty far off. Cape goals were scored by Steve Matalavage from Drew Mulcahy 5 minutes into the game,Jake Ashby from Mulcahy 17:00 and Mulcahy scored on an assist from Tyler Malloy 20 minutes into the game. Brent Hochrein got the win in goal. Cape improves to 10-1 on the season and next plays at St Thomas More on Thursday November 15 at 4 p.m Look for further details in the October 16 Friday edition of the Cape Gazette. Cape senior Steven Matalavage, left, works the ball past Delmar's Chance Watts. (Photo by: Dan Cook)
